\end_inset

which corresponds to the original state vector
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:reacting-navier-stokes-state"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 We then have the following theorem.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
The two-point numerical state function in Equation
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:numerical-state-EC-transformed"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

